Occurrences before and after fire

graphs

Overall occurrences of raptors and passerines between 1995-2020

The average number of occurrences reported 5 years before fire and 5 years after fire. Zeros were added to years when no occurrences were reported.

###data for over-time for burned sites

data_ot_b <- data_r %>% filter(yearsSinceFire >0) %>% 
  dplyr::select(c("ez_taxa", "funcGroup", "individualCount", "obsYear", "desert", "fireID", "fireName", "fireYear", "fireMonth", "yearsSinceFire", "pre_or_post", "n_years", "ndvi")) %>% 
  group_by(desert, obsYear, fireID, fireYear, yearsSinceFire, ez_taxa, funcGroup, pre_or_post, n_years, ndvi) %>% 
  summarize(totalObs = n()) %>% 
  left_join(., filter(areas, treatmentGroup == "burned"), by = "desert") %>% #add area
  mutate(stzdObs = ceiling((totalObs/area_km2)*10000)) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% group_by(desert)
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'desert', 'obsYear', 'fireID', 'fireYear',
## 'yearsSinceFire', 'ez_taxa', 'funcGroup', 'pre_or_post', 'n_years'. You can
## override using the `.groups` argument.
###data for over time for control

test2 <- data_ot_b %>% group_by(desert, fireYear) %>% 
  summarize(maxTime = max(yearsSinceFire))
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'desert'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.
yearsSinceFire <- c()
desert <- c()
fireYear <- c()

for (i in 1:nrow(test2)) {
   yearsSinceFire <-  c(yearsSinceFire, rep(1:test2$maxTime[i], 1))
  }

for (i in 1:nrow(test2)) {
   desert <-  c(desert, rep(test2$desert[i], each = test2$maxTime[i]))
  }

for (i in 1:nrow(test2)) {
   fireYear <-  c(fireYear, rep(test2$fireYear[i], each = test2$maxTime[i]))
  }


data_ot_c <- data.frame(desert, fireYear, yearsSinceFire) %>% 
  mutate(obsYear = fireYear + yearsSinceFire) %>% 
  filter(obsYear < 2021) %>% 
  left_join(., totalObs, by = c("obsYear", "desert")) %>% 
  left_join(., filter(ndvi, treatmentGroup == "never burned"), by = c("desert", "obsYear")) %>%#add ndvi
  dplyr::select(-treatmentGroup) %>% 
  left_join(., filter(areas, treatmentGroup == "never burned"), by = "desert") %>% #add area
  mutate(stzdObs = ceiling((totalObs/area_km2)*10000), treatmentGroup = "control")

# data_ot <- rbind(data_ot_b, data_ot_c) %>% 
#   dplyr::select(-c(pre_or_post, n_years))

data_ot_b_avg <- data_ot_b %>% group_by(desert, yearsSinceFire, ez_taxa, funcGroup) %>% 
  summarize(avgObs_burn = mean(stzdObs))
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'desert', 'yearsSinceFire', 'ez_taxa'. You
## can override using the `.groups` argument.
data_ot_c_avg <- data_ot_c %>% group_by(desert, yearsSinceFire, ez_taxa, funcGroup) %>% 
  summarize(avgObs_con = mean(stzdObs))
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'desert', 'yearsSinceFire', 'ez_taxa'. You
## can override using the `.groups` argument.
##join control and burn
data_ot <- left_join(filter(data_ot_b_avg), filter(data_ot_c_avg), by = c("desert", "yearsSinceFire", "funcGroup", "ez_taxa")) %>% 
  mutate(diffObs = avgObs_burn - avgObs_con)

#create pseudo absence
data_ot_psab <- full_join(data_ot_b_avg, data_ot_c_avg, by = c("desert", "yearsSinceFire", "funcGroup", "ez_taxa")) %>%  
  mutate(avgObs_con = ifelse(is.na(avgObs_con), 0, avgObs_con),
         avgObs_burn = ifelse(is.na(avgObs_burn), 0, avgObs_burn),
         diffObs = avgObs_burn - avgObs_con)
